Author-Name:    Leach, John
Title:   Rational Speculation. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 131-44
Issue: 1
Volume: 99
Year: 1991
Month:  February 
Abstract:
  The stationary equilibrium of an overlapping generations economy in which
 agents trade a single asset is examined. If agents live for only two
 periods, the selling prices follow an identically and independently
 distributed process. If agents live for more than two periods, the selling
 prices follow a Markov process. An implication of the model is that price
 bubbles can occur in a stationary, rational expectations equilibrium.  Copyright 1991 by University of Chicago Press.
